Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and finely dice @yellow onion{1}(peeled and finely diced). Trim and quarter @zucchini{1}(trimmed and quartered lengthwise); thinly slice into quarter-moons. Dice @tomato{2}(diced into ½-inch pieces). Pick @parsley{¼%ounce}(picked from stems and roughly chopped) leaves from stems; roughly chop leaves.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a large, preferably ovenproof, pan over medium-high heat. Add onion, @salt{¼%tsp}, and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender and lightly browned, ~{3-6%minutes}.

Add another drizzle of oil, zucchini, @salt{¾%tsp}, and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until zucchini is softened, ~{4-7%minutes}.

Add @tomato paste{1.5%ounce}, @Italian seasoning{1%tbsp}, half the @chili powder{½%tsp}, and half the tomatoes. Cook, stirring, until tomato paste is darkened, ~{30-60%seconds}.

> While veggies cook, pat chicken dry with paper towels and season all over with salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a second large pan over medium-high heat. Add @Italian chicken sausage mix{9%ounce} and cook, stirring frequently, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Transfer to a #plate{}.

While veggies cook, halve @demi-baguette{1} lengthwise. Brush cut sides with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp}; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toast, cut sides up, directly on oven rack until golden, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Transfer toasted baguette to a #cutting board{}. Dice into 1-inch croutons.

Add @cannellini beans{1%15oz can} and their liquid, @mushroom stock concentrate{1}(and @veggie stock concentrate{1}), and @water{¼%cup} to pan with veggies. Cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly reduced, ~{2-3%minutes}. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Remove from heat. Stir in remaining tomatoes.

> TIP: If your pan isn't ovenproof, transfer everything to a small baking dish now.

Stir chicken or sausage into pan along with remaining tomatoes.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @ricotta cheese{4%oz} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp}. Season with @salt{¼%tsp} and pepper.

Dollop ricotta over skillet. Top with croutons and @Parmesan cheese{3%tbsp}.

Bake on top rack until cheese melts, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Garnish skillet with chopped parsley. Divide between plates or serve directly from pan.

> Chicken Sausage is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.